\subsection{Primes of good and bad reduction of a hypergeometric motive}
\begin{definition}\label{hgm.good_prime}
\uses{hgm.conductor,hgm.motive,hgm.tame,hgm.wild}
A **prime of bad reduction** or **bad prime** of a {{ KNOWL('hgm.motive', 'hypergeometric motive') }} \(M\) is a prime dividing the {{ KNOWL('hgm.conductor', 'conductor') }} of \(M\). A bad prime is either {{ KNOWL('hgm.tame', 'tame') }} or {{ KNOWL('hgm.wild', 'wild') }}.

A **prime of good reduction** or **good prime** is a prime that is not a bad prime, i.e., a prime that does not divide the conductor.
\end{definition}


